Thrall: "Then it's a good thing I'm one hell of a shaman."

Varian: The Horde. Of course.

Jaina: I have no idea what Thrall sees in you.

Jaina: If you orcs won't serve as our minions, then the humans will.

Rehgar: Great... it's you.

Gul'dan: So this is what became of my Horde? <scoff> I should crush you like a gnat.
Tyrande: We remain allied through convenience. Do not make it, inconvenient.
Tyrande: The goddess seems to be testing my resolve...
Kerrigan: "Let's go tear them apart."
Kerrigan: "You, huh? This could be fun."
Malthael: "<angry exhale>"
Malthael: "You..."
Alarak: "<laugh> I believe I like you. How unexpected."
Alarak: "Oh, I sense within you a fire others lack. Let's hope this proves interesting."
